            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-247-person1975">
                  JOHN 
                  HARDY
               <interp inst="t18291029-247-person1975" type="surname" value="HARDY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-247-person1975" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-247-person1975" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman of Islington. At a quarter-past four o'clock in the morning of the 13th of September, I met the prisoner in the back road with this piece of timber under his arm - I said, "Mate, what is this?" he dropped it, and offered me 1s. 6d. to let him go, but I would not; he was then within a few hundred yards of the prosecutor's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-247-person1976">
                  RICHARD 
                  CHAPMAN
               <interp inst="t18291029-247-person1976" type="surname" value="CHAPMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-247-person1976" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-247-person1976" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , JUN. This was my father's property; his name is Richard. I had seen it safe in the brick field, but I cannot say when; the prisoner had been in our employ three years, but when we found he was a returned transport we discharged him, and since he has been in our employ we have lost twenty-two planks.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I took this bit of plank by order of the foreman to lay over a dirty ditch, for some of my children to get a penny if they could; the foreman said I might have it if I brought it back at night.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-247-person1977">
                  WILLIAM 
                  ELLIS
               <interp inst="t18291029-247-person1977" type="surname" value="ELLIS"></interp>
